But there can be no doubt, that, in the instance relied upon‚ Peer was simply a misprint for Feer. That Napier had so written his signature for the edition of 1645, the only instance of its occurrence, is put out of the question by the fact, that, before that date, he had been dead for eight-and-twenty years.
